  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (environmental gap variant)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. The pump is intended for deployment in operating-room environments subject to temperature variation (18–26°C), electromagnetic interference from adjacent surgical equipment, and ambient pressure fluctuations in high-altitude facilities. All validation experiments were conducted under controlled laboratory conditions at 22°C and atmospheric pressure; no environmental-sensitivity study has been performed and the operating envelope does not formally bound these parameters.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/cpb-hemolysis-mrl2",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cpb-cfd-hemolysis-worst-case",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/cfd-centrifugal-pump-hemolysis-v2",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-generic-pump-geometry",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/cpb-hemolysis-lab-measurements",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/cfd-mesh-convergence-study"
  ],
  "hasContextOfUse": {
    "decisionConsequence": "High",
    "description": "A CFD model is used to evaluate the sensitivity of pump-induced hemolysis to variations in component dimensions for a centrifugal blood pump used during cardiopulmonary bypass surgery. Model influence is MEDIUM (testing confirms results); decision consequence is HIGH (incorrect tolerance decision could impact clinical hemolysis levels). Model Risk Level 2. The device is deployed in operating theatres where ambient temperature ranges from 18°C to 26°C, electromagnetic interference from electrosurgical units and perfusion monitoring equipment is routinely present, and facilities at altitude (up to 2500 m above sea level) operate at reduced ambient pressure (~75 kPa). These environmental parameters have not been characterised as part of the validation programme.",
    "deviceClass": "Class II",
    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou1-cpb",
    "intendedUse": "Use CFD to identify worst-case operating conditions for hemolysis across 5 flow-speed combinations for a Class II CPB device. Results compared against predicate device hemolysis using relative hemolysis index (RH < 1 acceptance criterion).",
    "modelInfluence": "Medium",
    "name": "COU1: Cardiopulmonary bypass use (Class II)",
    "type": "ContextOfUse"
  },
  "hasValidationResult": [
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/cpb-vr-01-mesh-convergence",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Mesh convergence and discretisation error study",
      "description": "Grid-convergence index (GCI) study performed on three mesh densities (2.1M, 5.8M, 14.2M cells). GCI for shear-stress scalar < 3.2% on fine mesh. All runs executed in laboratory at 22°C, atmospheric pressure (101.3 kPa). No variation of ambient conditions was introduced."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/cpb-vr-02-hemolysis-bench",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Bench-top hemolysis validation against FDA pump experimental data",
      "description": "CFD-predicted normalised index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against published FDA benchtop measurements at five flow-speed operating points. Mean absolute error 8.4%. Experiments conducted in climate-controlled laboratory at 22 ± 0.5°C and 101.3 kPa. EM shielding present throughout; no EM interference scenario was tested. High-altitude or reduced-pressure conditions were not evaluated."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/cpb-vr-03-code-verification",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Numerical code verification against analytical solutions",
      "description": "Method of manufactured solutions (MMS) applied to the incompressible Navier-Stokes solver. Second-order spatial convergence confirmed. Verification conducted entirely in standard laboratory conditions; environmental factors not considered."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/cpb-vr-04-sensitivity-qoi",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Sensitivity analysis of QoI to inlet boundary conditions",
      "description": "One-at-a-time sensitivity study varying inlet flow rate ±15% and rotational speed ±10%. Relative hemolysis index RH remains below 1.0 across all tested combinations. Study performed under nominal lab conditions (22°C, 101.3 kPa); temperature-dependent blood viscosity changes at 18°C or 26°C were not explored."
    }
  ],
